\f1\b \cf2 \strokec2 N52SH
\f0\b0 \cf2 \strokec2  grade.\
Instead, N42EH degraded more. Ambient heat cannot selectively target the ruggedized grain boundaries of a specific magnet grade. Thermal neutrons, however, will preferentially target those boundaries due to Dysprosium's massive capture cross-section.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

